Grenadaâ€™s airport re-opened on 1 July to charter flights, on 15 July to regional commercial flights, and on 1 August to commercial flights from the UK, Europe and Canada. The planned resumption of direct British Airways flights on 14 October has been delayed. Virgin Atlantic is set to resume direct flights from the UK to Grenada from 26 October.
Caribbean Airlines started a regional service from Grenada to Barbados from 22 July and Inter Caribbean from 1 August.
If you are considering travelling by any direct routes you are responsible for ensuring that you meet all requirements for entry and onward travel of all countries and territories. Review the relevant country pages on FCDO Travel Advice before travel and check carefully any requirements for COVID testing before departure, to ensure that your test certificate, if required, will be accepted in your arrival country.
Returning to the UK
When you return, you must follow the rules for entering the UK. From 10 July those entering the UK from Grenada will not have to self- isolate on arrival.
Sign up for travel advice email alerts and follow the British High Commission in Bridgetown, Barbados, on Facebook and Twitter.
